stylometry:
Fixed cost models are to find the break-even point. To figure out how much we need to make or sell in order to cover our costs. an example of this would be if you were producing and selling cookies, how many cookies do you need to sell to cover your costs of making them.
Set covering models show us the smallest number possible that will cover the entire data set. And example is the Fire station problem where we had to determine how mant fire stations it takes to meet the given criteria and cover the entire data set.
